[4] Yemen
Date: Mon, 13 Jun 2005 10:49:10 +0100
From: Shirley Bannatyne <shirley.bannatyne@masta.org>
Source: Gulf News (Dubai), 5 Jun 2005 [edited]
<http://www.gulfnews.com/Search/searchResultsNF.asp?txtSearch=dengue&submit=Search>

Dengue fever kills 10 in Yemen
----------------------------------------
Dengue fever has killed 10 and infected 345 people in Yemen, according to a
confidential report.
Sources at the public health office in Shabwa province said 6 deaths were
reported from the Bayhan area and 4 from Radhoom until May 29.
However, the Shabwa local authorities declined to comment on the number of
deaths and whether they are dengue fever cases for sure or not.
Last week, authorities in Shabwa discussed measures to control the spread
of the disease.
The meeting approved the setting up of facilities for following up and
registering the cases in the 5 affected areas in the eastern provinces.
Earlier this year, hundreds of people were infected by the disease in the
coastal province of Hodeida [see ref:20050310.0709. - Mod.RY]
[Byline: Nasser Arrabyee]
--
Shirley Bannatyne
<shirley.bannatyne@masta.org>
